info: Flores is the MOC from Pflugerville and College Station

Congressman Carter is the ranking member of the Military Construction and Veterans Affairs Subcommittee on Appropriations and also to serves on the Appropriations Defense Subcommittee. He is Co-Chairman of the bipartisan House Army Caucus, and he is the Secretary of the House Republican Conference.
Engel is the senior Representative from New York on the Energy and Commerce Committee, and the Representative from New York on the Subcommittee on Energy and the Environment.

Representative Zoe Lofgren has served California's 19th District for over 24 years. She is a Democrat who chairs the Committee on House Administration and the Subcommittee on Immigration Policy and Enforcement. Lofgren believes that climate change is an extremely serious threat that must be addressed, however she is not a cosponsor of the Energy Innovation and Carbon Dividend Act.

Congresswoman Eleanor Holmes Norton, now in her fifteenth term as the Congresswoman for the District of Columbia, is the Chair of the House Subcommittee on Highways and Transit. She serves on two committees: the Committee on Oversight and Reform and the Committee on Transportation and Infrastructure.

Ann McLane Kuster was first elected to the House of Representatives to represent New Hampshire’s Second Congressional District in November of 2012, and she was sworn into office on January 3, 2013. She came to Washington determined to put an end to the gridlock, and during her time in office she has established a record of working across the aisle to get things done for her constituents in the Granite State.
Born and raised in Manchester, Chris Pappas is a small business owner and community-minded leader who has taken a principal role in addressing some of New Hampshire’s most pressing challenges.

Serving his eighth term in the U.S. House of Representatives, Cuellar represents Texas’ 28th congressional district, including Laredo, Mission, Rio Grande City, and San Antonio. Cuellar is the only Texas Democrat on the U.S. House Appropriations Committee. As one of eight children born to migrant farm workers in Laredo, Texas, Cuellar was raised with a passion for education and an unwavering work ethic. He is the most degreed member of Congress.

Allred is an attorney and former American football linebacker who played for the Tennessee Titans of the National Football League (NFL). Allred left football to pursue a degree in law, receiving his J.D. from the University of California, Berkeley, followed by positions in both the Obama administration and the U.S. Attorney's office. Collin Allred defeated incumbent Republican Pete Sessions in 2018. Colin Allred supported HR9 (Climate Action Now Act of 2019).
